# Intuition
<!-- Describe your first thoughts on how to solve this problem. -->
First we try to remove the spaces form the back. Then we try to find the first space starting from the last letter or if there is only one word, we go to the start of the string.

# Approach
<!-- Describe your approach to solving the problem. -->
1. There is an **i** which eliminates the spaces from behind. If there aren't any, **i** stays in last position.
2. The pointer **j** finds the first space starting from pointer **i** or goes till the string's beginning if there is only one word.
3. We return **(i-j)**.

# Complexity
- Time complexity:
<!-- Add your time complexity here, e.g. $$O(n)$$ -->
_O(n)_

- Space complexity:
<!-- Add your space complexity here, e.g. $$O(n)$$ -->
_O(1)_

# Code
```
class Solution {
public:
    int lengthOfLastWord(string s) {
        int n = s.length();
        int i;
        for(i = n-1;i>=0;i--){
            if(s[i] != ' ')
                break;
        }
        int j;
        for(j=i;j>=0;j--){
            if(s[j] == ' ')
                break;
        }
        return (i-j);
    }
};
```

